_header: We ladies three all by one consent
Subjects: pageant verses; Henry VI, return to London, 1432; occasional verse
_description: Pageant verses by Nature, Grace, and Fourteen Virgins, at the return of Henry VI to London, A.D. 1432, in Fabyan’s Chronicle, Part VII, Septima Pars, Henrici Sexti — three stanzas rhyme royal

HarEng766.First Lines:
We ladies three Alle by one ConcentThre goostly Giftes hevynly and
                    divyne…
HarEng766.Last Lines:
…In vertuous liffe with honour to procedeThat thy ii Ceptirs
                    thow may well Possede
